    "body": "The following shows it is possible to enter `Ex` mode but it is not possible to get out of it.\r\n```python\r\n>>> import neovim\r\n>>> n = neovim.attach(\"child\", argv=['/opt/homebrew/bin/nvim', \"--clean\", \"--embed\", \"--headless\"])\r\n>>> n.api.get_mode()\r\n{'mode': 'n', 'blocking': False}\r\n>>> n.input(\"Q\")\r\n1\r\n>>> n.api.get_mode()\r\n{'mode': 'ce', 'blocking': False}\r\n>>> n.input(\"vi\")\r\n2\r\n>>> n.api.get_mode()\r\n{'mode': 'ce', 'blocking': False}\r\n>>> n.input(\":vi\")\r\n3\r\n>>> n.api.get_mode()\r\n{'mode': 'ce', 'blocking': False}\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
